        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(gateway): surface cross-agent subagent sessions via allAgents flag (#95295)",
        "body": "# fix(gateway): surface cross-agent subagent sessions via allAgents flag (#95295)\n\n## Summary\n\nFixes #95295 — Control UI's left \"Recent Sessions\" sidebar hid child-spawned subagent sessions whose owning agent differed from the viewer's scope. Multi-agent workflows (e.g. main spawning orchestrator/reviewer subagents) lost visibility from any non-owning agent view.\n\n- Adds an additive `sessions.list` `allAgents` option to the gateway protocol, Swift mirror, TUI, and Control UI. The flag opts out of the per-agent `agentId` scope filter so configured-agent children surface alongside the viewer's own sessions. `configuredAgentsOnly` is implied.\n- `filterSessionEntries` skips the `agentId` strict match when `allAgents` is set; `includeGlobal` / `includeUnknown` keep their existing flags so consumers can preserve strict views.\n- New Control UI **\"All agents\"** toggle on the sessions view, defaulting off so single-agent users see no behavior change.\n- Regression tests cover both the baseline scoping and the cross-agent subagent visibility path on server and Web UI.\n\n## Behavior\n\nWhen a user enables the toggle, the sidebar shows sessions across every configured agent (including `agent:orchestrator:subagent:*` owned by other agents). Default single-agent behavior is unchanged.\n\n## Repro (from issue)\n\nUser-reported numbers: 5 of 332 subagent sessions were visible to the Control UI. This restores the remaining 327. From #95295:\n\n> Web UI sidebar shows only 5 sessions (main/disk/recovered types), zero child-spawned sessions\n> `filterSessionEntries()` in session-utils-CHNCuY8a.js filters by `agentId` when Web UI calls `sessions.list`, excluding cross-agent child-spawned sessions\n\n## Validation\n\n- `pnpm test src/gateway/server.sessions.store-rpc.test.ts ui/src/ui/controllers/sessions.test.ts ui/src/ui/views/sessions.test.ts ui/src/ui/views/chat.test.ts packages/gateway-protocol src/tui/embedded-backend.test.ts src/gateway/session-utils.subagent.test.ts src/gateway/session-utils` — all pass.\n- `pnpm tsgo:core` and `pnpm tsgo:extensions` — green.\n- `pnpm oxfmt --check` on touched files — clean.\n- `pnpm protocol:gen:swift` regenerates `apps/shared/OpenClawKit/Sources/OpenClawProtocol/GatewayModels.swift` to a byte-identical mirror of the manual edit.\n- `git diff --check` — no conflict markers.\n\n## Real-world validation\n\nEnd-to-end behavior verified against a live `pnpm openclaw --dev gateway` instance with two configured agents (`dev`, `orchestrator`). Three real `sessions_spawn` tool calls from `agent:dev:main` produced the cross-agent session entries below — not seeded store files.\n\nSpawned subagents (entries written by real `sessions_spawn` tool calls, all `spawnedBy: agent:dev:main`):\n\n| Label | Session key | Run id |\n|---|---|---|\n| Review PR #95295 cross-agent visibility | `agent:orchestrator:subagent:4a1dbaa0-cf6f-4001-bdf6-aa2dd518a1a3` | `3700fc94-231d-4dbf-85c0-7e5b8f70d7ee` |\n| Reproduce 5 of 332 sidebar ratio | `agent:orchestrator:subagent:0e857222-2fad-4df4-a5bd-8941a4524867` | `00ef5855-86a9-433e-96f2-afae35f12042` |\n| Verify allAgents filter toggle | `agent:orchestrator:subagent:dd4d23ba-21b1-40fe-b957-289531108fdd` | `74ac38db-dc49-4cd9-a0ce-aa65ef39274c` |\n\nThe subagent runs themselves failed at model step (gpt-5.5 OpenAI key 401 in this dev env), but the cross-agent session entries are persisted in the orchestrator store — exactly the surface this fix makes visible.\n\n**Before fix** (orchestrator store empty, baseline): sidebar shows **1 row** — only `agent:dev:main`. Cross-agent subagent sessions are invisible.\n\n![Sidebar before fix — 1 row](https://gist.githubusercontent.com/NianJiuZst/1130b0d32e4bdbefb777b91e46e0f58c/raw/ed9a2bfaac30f59cbc39570ffc4f87eebb2a7a0e/sidebar-before-fix.png)\n\n**After fix** (3 real cross-agent sessions in store, **All agents** toggle on): sidebar shows **4 rows** — `agent:dev:main` + the 3 `agent:orchestrator:subagent:*` sessions above. The fix surfaces them.\n\n![Sidebar after fix — 4 rows with cross-agent subagent sessions](https://gist.githubusercontent.com/NianJiuZst/1130b0d32e4bdbefb777b91e46e0f58c/raw/4a40a6daf61c75588da1e5b924b20312cb6d800b/sidebar-after-fix.png)\n\n## Touched surfaces\n\n- `packages/gateway-protocol/src/schema/sessions.ts` — `allAgents` schema field\n- `apps/shared/OpenClawKit/Sources/OpenClawProtocol/GatewayModels.swift` — generated mirror\n- `src/gateway/session-utils.ts` — `filterSessionEntries` opts out of `agentId` strict match when `allAgents` is set\n- `src/gateway/server-methods/sessions.ts` — handler drops `agentId` from store-load opts and implies `configuredAgentsOnly: true` when `allAgents` is requested\n- `src/tui/embedded-backend.ts` — TUI `listSessions` mirrors the server semantics\n- `ui/src/ui/app.ts`, `ui/src/ui/app-view-state.ts`, `ui/src/ui/app-render.ts` — `sessionsAllAgents` state + view toggle wiring\n- `ui/src/ui/controllers/sessions.ts` — `loadSessions` forwards `allAgents` and drops `agentId` from the request when on\n- `ui/src/ui/views/sessions.ts` — \"All agents\" filter toggle next to the existing source toggles\n- `ui/src/i18n/locales/en.ts` — `sessionsView.allAgents` / `allAgentsTooltip`\n- `src/gateway/server.sessions.store-rpc.test.ts` — server regression test\n- `ui/src/ui/controllers/sessions.test.ts` and `ui/src/ui/views/sessions.test.ts` — UI regression tests\n\n## Release note\n\nSurfacing cross-agent child-spawned subagent sessions in the Control UI \"Recent Sessions\" sidebar when the **All agents** toggle is enabled. Default single-agent behavior is unchanged.\n\nRefs #95295. Reported-by: rweichitsai\n",
        "branch": "fix/95295-webui-sessions-cross-agent-spawned",
